    <text>
        <body>
            
            <div1 type="letter">
                
                <pb facs="nei.j4a.26a.3"/>
                
                <note type="curatorial">71 Neihardt Collection</note>
                
                <note type="recipient">Written 11 days before Mona went <hi rend="caps">J.N.</hi></note>
                
                <fw type="curatorial">3</fw>
                
                <opener>
                    <dateline>
                        April 6, 1958
                        1511 Dorland St.
                        <unclear>Whittier</unclear>, Calif
                    </dateline>
                
                    <salute>Dear Dr Neihardt,</salute>
                </opener>
                <p>I have just finished reading "Black Elk Speaks," I could not help but write to you and thank you for the many hours you gave to me while I attended the Univeristy of Missouri. The book brought back the many wonderful memories of your lectures in poetry, the afternoons at your farm with your friendly family, and the countless discussions <del/><add>of</add> values.</p>
                
                <p>The main purpose of the letter is to let you know that I still think often of you and your family. I hope that everyone is in good health. I especially want you to know that the values and understandings I learned from you are still with me and that many of them still serve me faithfully as guides preceeding me into each day's new journey.</p>
                
                <p>I was in your first class of Poety<sic>Poetry</sic> at Missouri back in 49' and 50', when I graduated. Although I learned to evaluate and appreciate poetry, I am, unfortunately, still unable to write it. So although I did not "become a poet," I thought I would write and again thank you for the most important lessons in your class, these values in understanding I still retain. If you do remember me, I am now moved and have a 15 month old daughter, Nina.</p>
                <closer>
                    <salute>Cordially,</salute>
                    
                    <signed>Bill Kotoff</signed>
                </closer>
                
            </div1>
